emails.subject: Re: ecmwf not working for some countries: Black sea and middle east at least
emails.to: Jebrane Ben Salem; Pablo Figueroa; Support Dnext
emails.body_text:
as per the ECMWF Open Data documentation, only a limited number of forecast time steps are available for the 06Z and 18Z runs


https://www.ecmwf.int/en/forecasts/datasets/open-data
Open data - ECMWF <https://www.ecmwf.int/en/forecasts/datasets/open-data> 
These products are a subset of the full Catalogue of ECMWF Real-time Products and are based on the medium-range (high-resolution and ensemble) and seasonal forecast models.. IFS data are released 1 hour after the real-time dissemination schedule.AIFS data are released as soon the data are produced. For further details about the available AIFS products, see the dataset description.
www.ecmwf.int

We are showing all the data that we currently have access to.
________________________________

From: Jebrane Ben Salem <jebrane.bensalem@dnext.io>
Sent: 04 March 2025 18:02
To: Pablo Figueroa <pablo.figueroa@dnext.io>; Support Dnext <support@dnext.io>; Martin Keller <martin.keller@dnext.io>
Subject: Re: ecmwf not working for some countries: Black sea and middle east at least 
 
I'm adding @Martin Keller <mailto:martin.keller@dnext.io> .
As discussed with Martin earlier, the ECMWF 6Z data is incomplete for 06Z for all countries
@Martin Keller <mailto:martin.keller@dnext.io> , please correct me if I’m mistaken

________________________________
